# Generated metadata snapshots (regenerated by scripts/export_metadata.py).
# Marked linguist-generated so GitHub folds them in PRs and drops them from
# language stats.
#
# reaches.json (pure geometry) and huc_name.csv (the HUC6+HUC8 WBD lookup) are also
# -diff: a textual diff is never useful, so git shows "Binary files differ"
# instead of thousands of lines. reach.csv is NOT -diff — its bulk is the
# machine-generated gradient_profile column, but the other ~37 columns are
# hand-edited reach metadata (description, notes, optimal_flow, …) that a
# reviewer should still be able to read in `git diff` / a PR.
data/db/reaches.json  -diff linguist-generated
data/db/reach.csv           linguist-generated
data/db/huc_name.csv  -diff linguist-generated
